You need to iterate through each items in the JSON array sent by the API to construct the desired output.

First use the built in ```Date()``` functions to get year from each items. Then construct an object where ```key``` is unique ```year``` in given set of data, then group element when year is matched. Once grouped, it can be transformed to any structure.

**Sample Code:**

```
/* STEP 1: Create a temp object to store year wise data - Grouping */
 const obj = {};
 data.map(item =&gt; { 
   const year = new Date(item.date).getFullYear();
   obj[year] ? obj[year].push(item) : obj[year] = [item];
 });

/* STEP 2: Transform data to desired format - Transforming */
 const result = Object.keys(obj).map(year =&gt; ({year: year, contents: obj[year]}));


```

**JSFiddle:**

https://jsfiddle.net/79n3btr0/1/

```js
const newData = [];

data.forEach(entry =&gt; {
  const year = entry.date.split(&#39;-&#39;)[0];
  if (!newData[year]) newData[year] = [];
  newData[year].push(entry);
});

/* newData is in this format:
{
  &#39;2014&#39;: [{..}, {..}],
  &#39;2015&#39;: [{..}, {..}]
}
*/

// To get your desired format we do this
const finalData = Object.keys(newData).map(year =&gt; ({ year: year, entries: newData[year] }));
```

